# halo-class — CS 4824 class project

Predicting protein subcellular localization from amino-acid sequences. The
task is decomposed into 10 binary classifiers (one per compartment). Built on
the [DeepLoc 2.0](https://services.healthtech.dtu.dk/services/DeepLoc-2.0/)
dataset.

**Read [`SPEC.md`](SPEC.md)** for the full specification and
[`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) for the repo guide. Agents starting work should read
[`KICKOFF.md`](KICKOFF.md) first.

## Quickstart

```bash
pip install -e .
make test       # 5/5 tests
make spec       # full classical comparison panel + figures (~30–60 min CPU)
```

## Layout

```
SPEC.md          — what to build and how to evaluate it
AGENTS.md        — repo guide for agents (invariants, gotchas, where to find things)
KICKOFF.md       — first-prompt template for the agent
Data/            — DeepLoc 2.0 CSVs (source of truth, never modified)
specData/        — engineered per-protein features (pre-built; can regenerate)
halo/            — Python package (data loaders + spec-track models)
tests/           — pytest smoke tests
runs/            — produced experiment outputs (gitignored)
Makefile         — one-line entry points
```
